article.headline: Wagner 78, Fairleigh Dickinson 69
article.story: HACKENSACK, N.J. -- Joey Mundweiler scored 18 points and Wagner pulled away in the final two minutes to defeat Fairleigh Dickinson 78-69 Monday night. Justin Drummond added 17 points for the Seahawks (9-4, 2-1 Northeast Conference) and Jamal Smith scored 16. Fairleigh Dickinson's (2-11, 2-2) Cameron Tyler led all scorers with 20 points. Wagner led 66-64 after FDU's Sean Baptiste made two free throws with 2:31 remaining. The Seahawks then scored 12 of the game's final 17 points. Wagner made nine of 19 3-point attempts. Mundweiler was 4-for-7 from behind the arc. Alvin Mofunanya added 18 points for FDU.
